# Project-root .env — gitignored. Copy to .env and fill in real values.
#
# Loaded automatically by `pnpm -C server dev` (via Node's --env-file-if-exists
# flag). For the compiled paths (`pnpm exec ledger`, `node dist/bin/ledger.js`)
# you must either export these variables yourself or run the binary under
# `node --env-file=.env …`.

# Anthropic auth for the agent-dispatcher's `claude` subprocess.
# Required for `06-agent-dispatcher`'s dispatch flow (parent §Acceptance
# check items 3–6).
#
# CRITICAL — credential-format compatibility:
#   The executor's spawn flags (currently `--bare`) determine which credential
#   formats are accepted. As of v1, `--bare` strictly accepts only API-format
#   keys (`sk-ant-api03-…`) from ANTHROPIC_API_KEY or apiKeyHelper.
#
#   OAUTH TOKENS DO NOT WORK with the current `--bare` configuration:
#     - `claude setup-token` mints an OAuth-style token (`sk-ant-oat01-…`,
#       ~108 chars) tied to your subscription's OAuth flow.
#     - Pasting that here will fail at dispatch time with the message
#       `Invalid API key · Fix external API key` (written to stdout, not
#       stderr — see 03-claude-code-executor's Open Issue on
#       stdout-not-captured-in-failure-reason).
#
#   Two ways to fill this in correctly:
#     1. **API-credit (recommended)** — create a key at
#        https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys (format `sk-ant-api03-…`).
#        Billing draws from API credits.
#     2. **Subscription via dropped `--bare`** — if `--bare` has been removed
#        from `spawn.ts` (parent D17 amended), `setup-token`'s OAuth token
#        works because claude's normal auth path (OAuth/keychain) is restored.
#        Check the dispatcher's spawn flags before relying on this.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional: override the API server port (default 4180).
# LEDGER_PORT=4180

# Optional: gate the env-gated real-claude smoke test in 03-claude-code-executor
# (off by default; the fake-claude fixture covers the integration path mechanically).
# LEDGER_SMOKE_TESTS=1
